<SLUG> BC-LADN-BUDGET </SLUG>
  
<TEXT>
<P>
   The Los Angeles Daily News plans to move the following general
stories for use by NYTimes News Service clients, AMs and PMs of
Sunday, June 6 and thereafter. For questions about stories, contact
Susan Leh at the Daily News, (818) 713-3702
</P>
<P>
   ARMENIA-DOCTORS (Los Angeles) _ Doctors from Armenia are
visiting Glendale Memorial Hospital for six weeks to learn how to
improve the health care management in their country. It's so
lacking in Armenia that their government-run hospitals do not have
admitting policies and no emergency rooms. The CEO of Memorial has
also visited Armenia to help them and to help Memorial be more
Armenian-friendly. The hospital now offers Armenian patients
Armenina food and the Armenian cable channel. By Donna Huffaker.
(Will move in the ``n'' California and ``a'' national news file.)
</P>
<P>
   X X X
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
