<P>
   BBO-UMPIRE-DREAMS _ GAINESVILLE, Ga. _ Most fans go to Turner
Field to see Chipper Jones hit or Greg Maddux pitch. Not Jonathan
Merry. When the 18-year-old North Hall High School senior watches a
baseball game, his eyes never leave the umpires. He wants to be the
next Harry Wendelstedt, not Tom Glavine. The odds of reaching the
majors as an umpire are even longer than making it as a player. But
Merry knows about overcoming obstacles. He has done it all his
life. ``Everyone said I would never graduate from high school,''
Merry remembered. ``I've been proving people wrong for a long
time.'' Despite his reading disorder, Merry will graduate from
North Hall High School with honors Tuesday. He has already
graduated from umpire's school and hopes to be working in the minor
leagues by next season. (Curtright, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
27. WITH PHOTOS. MOVED
