<TEXT>
<P>
   The Los Angeles Daily News plans to add the following general
stories for use by NYTimes News Service clients, AMs and PMs of
Sunday, June 6 and thereafter. For questions about stories, contact
Susan Leh at the Daily News, (818) 713-3702
</P>
<P>
   TOXIC-CONTAMINATION (Los Angeles) _ Residents next to the
Belmont Learning Center were evacuated last week because of highly
poisonous hydrogen sulfide gas that surfaced after grading on the
campus. Firefighters and hazardous waste experts allowed the
residents to return, but a petroleum scientist studying the site
said the gas remains in high levels. By Greg Gittrich. (Will move
in the ``n'' California and ``a'' national news file.)
</P>
<P>
   TICKETS-ONLINE (Los Angeles) _ Sales of tickets over the
Internet gives scalpers the ability to almost instantly drain the
pool of lower-priced seats for popular events. By Ben Sullivan.
(Will move in the ``n'' California and ``a'' national news file.)
</P>
